          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The mono-energetic neutrons were generated",
                " using energetic deuteron beam from the accelerator to",
                " bombard a deuterium gas target. For neutron energies",
                " of 5.5 and 6.5 MeV, the corresponding neutron energy",
                " spreads (1 sigma) were 0.14 and 0.10 MeV,",
                " respectively. The beam current was about 2.0 uA",
                " throughout the measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "62-SM-144",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.95
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "+-----------------------------------------------------+",
                " Samples  Material  Isotopic     Thickness    Diameter",
                "                    enrichment(%) (ug/cm2)      (mm)",
                "-------------------------------------------------------",
                " 144Sm    144Sm2O3  95.0         4084 (Forward)   44.0",
                "                                 3177 (Backward)  44.0",
                " 238U     238U3O8   99.999       604.84           45.0",
                "+-----------------------------------------------------+"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The relative neutron flux was monitored using a",
                " BF3 long counter."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The alpha-particle detector is a twin gridded",
                " ionization chamber (GIC). Working gas of the GIC was",
                " Kr + 2.83% CO2, and the pressure is 2.02 atm for the",
                " alpha-particles to be stopped before reaching the",
                " grids."
              ]
            }
          ],
